<article class="content-page wrap">
    <header class="content-head">
        <p class="content-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="content-lead">
            How @Brand.Name handles your information. This is a plain-English summary for our early
            preview — we'll expand it before any public launch or app-store release.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
        <p class="legal-version">Version @Steeple.Web.Configuration.LegalDocuments.PrivacyVersion</p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>You can browse everything on @Brand.Name without an account. We use a session cookie to keep the
            site working and to understand, in aggregate, how the listings are browsed.</p>

        <h2>Your account</h2>
        <p>If you sign in, you do it with Google or Apple — we never see or store a password. From your
            sign-in we keep your name, your email address (Apple lets you hide it behind a relay address),
            and the fact that your account came from that provider. We use these to run your account and to
            let venues know who's asking about their space, nothing else.</p>
        <p>You can delete your account from the <a href="~/account">account page</a> at any time — your name
            and email are removed immediately, and you're signed out everywhere.</p>

        <h2>Contacting a venue</h2>
        <p>When you contact a venue, your message goes to that venue by email — you're emailing them directly,
            not through a @Brand.Name inbox. Anything you put in that message is shared with the venue, not with us.</p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>We set essential, first-party cookies only: a session cookie, and an encrypted sign-in cookie if
            you have an account. We don't use third-party advertising or cross-site tracking cookies.</p>

        <h2>What we don't do</h2>
        <p>We don't sell your data, and we don't share it with advertisers.</p>

        <h2>Your choices &amp; contact</h2>
        <p>You can browse without signing in or providing personal details. For any privacy question, or to
            ask us to remove information, get in touch via the <a href="~/about">about page</a>.</p>

        <p class="prose-note">This is a preview policy and will be replaced with a full, dated privacy policy
            before launch.</p>
    </div>
</article>
